Transnet to Reopen Second Freight Rail Line Following Derailment

-- B y   L a u r e n   v a n   d e r   W e s t h u i z e n
-- 
2011-04-08T10:05:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/transnet-reopens-second-freight-rail-line-to-richards-bay-after-derailment.html
Transnet Ltd.,  South Africa ’s state-
owned ports and freight rail utility, will reopen a second rail
line carrying coal to the Richards Bay terminal on the country’s
east coast later today, spokesman Sandile Simelane said by
mobile phone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
